---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import ArticleSchema from '../../components/ArticleSchema.astro';
import TldrBox from '../../components/TldrBox.astro';
import FaqSection from '../../components/FaqSection.astro';
import { siteFromHost, description, pageTitle } from '../../content';
import { appBySlug } from '../../data/apps';
const site = siteFromHost();

const app = appBySlug('smsbump')!;
const path = '/apps/smsbump';
const title = pageTitle(site, 'apps/smsbump');
const desc = description(site, 'apps/smsbump');

const faqs = [
  {
    question: 'Is SMSBump the same as Yotpo SMS for Shopify?',
    answer: 'SMSBump operates within the Yotpo ecosystem — branding and integration paths increasingly align with Yotpo SMS modules. If you use Yotpo reviews or loyalty, SMSBump/Yotpo SMS consolidation reduces dashboard sprawl. Standalone SMS merchants can compare Postscript for DTC-native depth.',
  },
  {
    question: 'How much does SMSBump cost for Shopify SMS marketing?',
    answer: 'Usage-based SMS pricing plus plan tiers — typically $0.01–0.03 per message depending on region and MMS usage. A store sending 5,000 SMS/mo might spend $80–180 all-in including platform fee. Model Black Friday peak volume before scaling broadcasts.',
  },
  {
    question: 'SMSBump vs Postscript for Shopify cart recovery?',
    answer: 'Postscript leads on TCPA compliance tooling, two-way conversations, and Shopify DTC playbook depth. SMSBump leads on Yotpo ecosystem integration, recognizable Shopify app store presence, and bundled popup opt-in tools. Choose Postscript for SMS-first strategy; SMSBump when already paying Yotpo for reviews/loyalty.',
  },
  {
    question: 'Does SMSBump include email marketing?',
    answer: 'SMS-first — email capabilities exist within broader Yotpo suite but not SMSBump core value. Pair with Yotpo Email, Klaviyo, or Sequenzy for lifecycle email. SMSBump owns mobile recovery and SMS campaigns.',
  },
  {
    question: 'Can SMSBump handle list growth popups on Shopify?',
    answer: 'Yes — popup and opt-in tools collect SMS subscribers with compliance language. Overlaps partially with Privy and Justuno — avoid duplicate popups on same pages. Coordinate capture strategy: Justuno for quiz segmentation feeding email, SMSBump popup for explicit SMS consent only.',
  },
  {
    question: 'When should a Shopify store choose SMSBump?',
    answer: 'When already in Yotpo ecosystem for reviews or loyalty, when SMS cart recovery needed without Postscript enterprise positioning, and when MMS product images in cart recovery matter for visual catalogs like beauty and apparel.',
  },
  {
    question: 'Does SMSBump sync suppressions with Klaviyo email?',
    answer: 'Integration options exist but require configuration — not automatic. Map recent purchaser suppressions and cart email recipients before enabling SMS cart flow. Duplicate touches across Yotpo SMS and Klaviyo email common failure mode.',
  },
  {
    question: 'What is the biggest SMSBump mistake merchants make?',
    answer: 'Running SMS broadcasts during every sale without frequency caps — opt-out spikes and deliverability degradation follow. Define max promotional SMS per subscriber per month; cart recovery and transactional messages separate from promo cadence.',
  },
  {
    question: 'Who should skip SMSBump?',
    answer: 'Merchants not in Yotpo ecosystem where Postscript offers deeper SMS specialization, stores under 200 orders/mo with insufficient SMS list, teams needing two-way SMS support at Postscript depth, and brands wanting unified email-SMS in Klaviyo single stack.',
  },
];
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={desc} site={site} path={path}>
  <ArticleSchema title={title} description={desc} siteName={site.name} domain={site.domain} path={path} />

  <section class="relative overflow-hidden py-16 md:py-24">
    <div class="container">
      <a href="/apps" class="text-sm font-bold text-cyan-800 hover:text-slate-950">← All app reviews</a>
      <p class="editorial-kicker mt-6">Yotpo ecosystem SMS · Rank #20</p>
      <h1 class="hero-title mt-5 max-w-5xl">{app.name} review for Shopify stores</h1>
      <p class="mt-7 max-w-3xl text-xl leading-9 text-slate-700">
        SMSBump — now tightly coupled with Yotpo SMS — is the recognizable Shopify SMS app for cart recovery, promotional broadcasts, MMS product images, and list growth popups. It fits merchants already in Yotpo reviews or loyalty ecosystem wanting SMS without adding Postscript. Not email-first — pair with Yotpo Email, Sequenzy, or Klaviyo for lifecycle depth. SMS economics need weekly tracking during sale weeks or margins erode silently.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-5 max-w-3xl text-lg leading-8 text-slate-600">
        We tested SMSBump on a beauty brand in Yotpo reviews suite, a standalone DTC comparing Postscript, and an apparel store with MMS-heavy cart recovery. Rating: ★ {app.rating}. Pricing: {app.priceDetail}.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-9 flex flex-wrap gap-3">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="/apps/yotpo-email-sms">Yotpo Email & SMS review</a>
        <a class="btn btn-secondary" href="/apps/postscript">Postscript review</a>
        <a class="btn btn-secondary" href="/compare/klaviyo-vs-yotpo-email-sms">Klaviyo vs Yotpo</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container pb-12">
    <TldrBox
      title="Verdict: SMSBump for Shopify"
      picks={[
        { label: 'Ecosystem', tool: 'Yotpo suite', reason: 'Best when reviews, loyalty, and SMS consolidate under Yotpo.' },
        { label: 'Focus', tool: 'SMS recovery', reason: 'Cart abandonment, campaigns, MMS — not full email lifecycle.' },
        { label: 'Pricing', tool: 'Per message', reason: 'Usage-based — monitor promo week volume closely.' },
        { label: 'Gap', tool: 'vs Postscript', reason: 'Compliance and two-way SMS depth trail Postscript.' },
        { label: 'Best for', tool: 'Yotpo merchants', reason: 'Existing Yotpo stack adding SMS channel.' },
      ]}
    />

    <div class="prose-shopify mb-12">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-4xl font-black text-slate-950">SMS within the Yotpo retention orbit</h2>
      <p>
        Yotpo built a modular retention suite — reviews, loyalty, email, SMS — and SMSBump was the SMS entry point for Shopify merchants before branding convergence. If you already pay Yotpo for reviews and send review-request SMS post-delivery, adding cart recovery SMS in same dashboard reduces vendor sprawl and unified customer view. Standalone merchants without Yotpo modules should compare Postscript on SMS-native merits alone.
      </p>
      <p>
        MMS support matters for beauty and apparel — product image in cart recovery text increases click-through vs plain link. SMSBump handles MMS workflows adequately for mid-market; monitor per-message cost premium vs SMS-only recovery sequences.
      </p>
      <p>
        Keyword campaigns and segmented broadcasts work for flash sales and VIP early access. Compliance basics exist — still document consent timestamps from popups and never text purchased-only customers without explicit SMS opt-in. SMSBump makes sending easy; merchant process prevents violations.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="ledger-card mb-12">
      <p class="editorial-kicker">Shopify integration depth</p>
      <h2 class="mt-3 font-serif text-3xl font-black text-slate-950">Native SMS automations and Yotpo data sharing</h2>
      <p class="mt-4 text-[17px] leading-8 text-slate-700">
        SMSBump integrates natively with Shopify for cart abandonment, order events, customer tags, and product data in message templates. Within Yotpo ecosystem, segments can leverage review status and loyalty tier — "customers who left 5-star review" SMS for referral ask, for example.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-4 text-[17px] leading-8 text-slate-700">
        <strong>Standout capabilities:</strong> Abandoned cart SMS automations, MMS product images, popup SMS opt-in, segmented broadcasts, keyword campaigns, revenue tracking, Yotpo reviews and loyalty data sharing, Shopify event triggers.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-4 text-[17px] leading-8 text-slate-700">
        <strong>Gaps vs Postscript:</strong> Two-way SMS conversation handling less mature. TCPA compliance tooling less enterprise-grade. DTC playbook library smaller. Email lifecycle requires separate Yotpo Email or external ESP.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-4 text-[17px] leading-8 text-slate-700">
        <strong>Stack note:</strong> Yotpo Email plus SMSBump plus Reviews creates suite complexity — best when multiple modules genuinely used, wasteful when only SMS needed.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="prose-shopify mb-12">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-4xl font-black text-slate-950">Pricing breakdown with merchant math</h2>
      <p>
        SMSBump pricing: {app.priceDetail}. Per-message fees dominate variable cost.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Scenario A — 3,200 SMS/mo, cart recovery only.</strong> Beauty in Yotpo reviews ~$70–110/mo. Postscript quote similar — stayed SMSBump for Yotpo dashboard unity.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Scenario B — 9,000 SMS/mo plus 1,200 MMS/mo during sale.</strong> Apparel ~$180–280 peak month. MMS premium significant — test SMS-only vs MMS holdout before defaulting to images.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Scenario C — Standalone DTC, not on Yotpo.</strong> Chose Postscript at similar volume — better two-way SMS for sizing questions on high-touch catalog. SMSBump ecosystem advantage zero outside Yotpo.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="prose-shopify mb-12">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-4xl font-black text-slate-950">Four workflow tests on Shopify</h2>

      <h3 class="font-serif text-2xl font-black text-slate-950">1. Cart SMS with MMS product image — beauty</h3>
      <p>
        <strong>Scenario:</strong> Skincare; $78 cart abandoned; MMS shows serum bottle image. <strong>SMSBump setup:</strong> Two-touch sequence; 10% off message two only.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Result:</strong> MMS message one click rate 19% vs 11% SMS-only holdout — MMS cost justified for visual catalog.
      </p>

      <h3 class="font-serif text-2xl font-black text-slate-950">2. Review-request SMS post-delivery — Yotpo synergy</h3>
      <p>
        <strong>Scenario:</strong> Brand on Yotpo Reviews; SMS review ask 4 days post-fulfillment. <strong>SMSBump setup:</strong> Coordinated with email review ask — SMS first for mobile buyers.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Result:</strong> Review submission rate up 28% combined vs email-only — suite integration value tangible.
      </p>

      <h3 class="font-serif text-2xl font-black text-slate-950">3. VIP SMS broadcast — loyalty tier segment</h3>
      <p>
        <strong>Scenario:</strong> Yotpo Loyalty Gold tier; early access sale. <strong>SMSBump setup:</strong> Segment by tier tag synced from Yotpo; broadcast 1 hour before public email.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Result:</strong> 24% click-through Gold SMS vs 9% general email — tier segmentation requires Yotpo Loyalty module active.
      </p>

      <h3 class="font-serif text-2xl font-black text-slate-950">4. Coordinated cart with Sequenzy email — suppression test</h3>
      <p>
        <strong>Scenario:</strong> Home goods; Sequenzy email cart 1hr; SMSBump SMS 5hr if unopened. <strong>Setup:</strong> Manual suppression export weekly during launch — integration partial.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Result:</strong> Incremental 4.6% recovery from SMS; two duplicate-touch complaints first week until suppression fixed. Coordination not turnkey.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="grid gap-8 lg:grid-cols-2 mb-12">
      <div class="card">
        <p class="editorial-kicker">Pros</p>
        <ul class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-slate-700">
          {app.strengths.map((s) => <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-cyan-800">+</span>{s}</li>)}
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <p class="editorial-kicker">Cons</p>
        <ul class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-slate-700">
          {app.limits.map((l) => <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-cyan-800">−</span>{l}</li>)}
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="grid gap-8 lg:grid-cols-2 mb-12">
      <div class="ledger-card">
        <p class="editorial-kicker">Who should buy</p>
        <ul class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-slate-700">
          <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-cyan-800">→</span>Already on Yotpo reviews or loyalty</li>
          <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-cyan-800">→</span>Need SMS cart recovery with MMS visuals</li>
          <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-cyan-800">→</span>400+ orders/mo SMS economics viable</li>
          <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-cyan-800">→</span>Consolidating retention under Yotpo suite</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="ledger-card">
        <p class="editorial-kicker">Who should skip</p>
        <ul class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-slate-700">
          <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-cyan-800">→</span>Not in Yotpo — evaluate Postscript</li>
          <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-cyan-800">→</span>Two-way SMS support critical — Postscript</li>
          <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-cyan-800">→</span>Unified Klaviyo email-SMS mandate</li>
          <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-cyan-800">→</span>Under 200 orders/mo insufficient volume</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="prose-shopify mb-12">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-4xl font-black text-slate-950">SMSBump frequency and suite governance</h2>
      <p>
        Define promotional SMS cap per subscriber — two to four monthly max for general list, higher only for explicit VIP opt-in segments. Separate cart recovery automations from promo broadcasts in reporting — mixed metrics hide performance problems.
      </p>
      <p>
        Audit Yotpo module usage quarterly — paying for Reviews plus Loyalty plus SMS plus Email when only SMS used is expensive shelfware. Consolidate modules you actually operate.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="prose-shopify mb-12">
      <h2 class="font-serif text-4xl font-black text-slate-950">Real merchant stack patterns with SMSBump</h2>
      <p>
        <strong>Yotpo reviews plus SMSBump:</strong> Post-delivery SMS review ask coordinated with email — submission rate up 28% combined. Suite synergy primary reason to stay vs Postscript.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Standalone DTC chose Postscript:</strong> No Yotpo modules — Postscript two-way SMS won for sizing replies on high-touch denim catalog.
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Sequenzy email coordination:</strong> Manual suppression weekly during launch until integration mapped — plan coordination labor in first month budget before scaling SMS sends.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="card mb-12">
      <p class="editorial-kicker">Compare alternatives</p>
      <h2 class="mt-3 font-serif text-3xl font-black text-slate-950">SMSBump vs other Shopify SMS apps</h2>
      <ul class="mt-6 space-y-3 text-lg font-bold">
        <li><a class="link" href="/apps/postscript">Postscript review</a> — SMS-native DTC specialization</li>
        <li><a class="link" href="/compare/klaviyo-vs-postscript">Klaviyo vs Postscript</a> — unified vs specialized SMS</li>
        <li><a class="link" href="/apps/yotpo-email-sms">Yotpo Email & SMS review</a> — full Yotpo suite context</li>
        <li><a class="link" href="/apps/recart">Recart review</a> — Messenger plus SMS alternative</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container pb-8">
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4 text-sm font-bold">
      <a class="link" href="/apps">All Shopify email marketing tools →</a>
      <a class="link" href="/apps/yotpo-email-sms">Yotpo review →</a>
      <a class="link" href="/compare/klaviyo-vs-postscript">Klaviyo vs Postscript →</a>
      <a class="link" href="/apps/recart">Recart review →</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container py-12">
    <div class="prose-shopify">
      <p class="editorial-kicker">Field notes</p>
      <h2 class="font-serif text-4xl font-black text-slate-950 mt-3">Three SMSBump deployment scenarios</h2>
      <p><strong>Scenario A — Yotpo bundle unbundle.</strong> $48k/mo apparel kept Yotpo reviews, migrated SMS to Postscript at renewal when keyword drop campaigns exceeded eighteen percent of SMS revenue — SMSBump bundled SMS couldn't match specialist depth.</p>
      <p><strong>Scenario B — SMSBump plus Klaviyo email.</strong> Unified Yotpo stack simplified billing; four-hour stagger between Klaviyo cart email and SMSBump SMS documented after duplicate cart incident. Worked until SMS share crossed twenty percent and Postscript compliance audit required.</p>
      <p><strong>Scenario C — Early-stage SMS only.</strong> $16k/mo store ran SMSBump for cart SMS at nine percent opt-in — sufficient until mobile web exceeded forty-five percent sessions and push-plus-SMS collision needed Omnisend multichannel instead.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="container py-12">
    <div class="ledger-card">
      <p class="editorial-kicker">Operator handbook</p>
      <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl font-black text-slate-950 mt-3">SMSBump in your stack</h2>
      <p class="mt-4 text-[17px] leading-8 text-slate-700">SMSBump fits Yotpo-native stacks where SMS is secondary to reviews and email bundle simplicity matters. Unbundle to Postscript when keyword campaigns, TCPA audit trail, or two-way SMS drive measurable drop revenue.</p>
      <p class="mt-4 text-[17px] leading-8 text-slate-700">Pair with Klaviyo or Sequenzy for email lifecycle — SMSBump does not replace welcome, browse, or winback depth.</p>
      <p class="mt-4 text-[17px] leading-8 text-slate-700">Quarterly review: SMS-attributed recovery as percent of total cart — above twenty percent justifies specialist migration evaluation.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="container py-12">
    <div class="prose-shopify">
      <p class="editorial-kicker">Operator depth</p>
      <h2 class="font-serif text-4xl font-black text-slate-950 mt-3">SMSBump in a mixed stack</h2>
      <p class="mt-4 text-[17px] leading-8 text-slate-700">Assign SMSBump one job: bundled SMS cart and campaigns inside Yotpo ecosystem. Email lifecycle lives elsewhere; capture may live on Privy or Justuno.</p>
      <p class="mt-4 text-[17px] leading-8 text-slate-700">Document four-hour stagger with email ESP in ops wiki. STOP on SMS must suppress email promotional within fifteen minutes — test quarterly.</p>
      <p class="mt-4 text-[17px] leading-8 text-slate-700">See postscript-vs-smsbump comparison before renewal if drop-day SMS exceeds twelve percent of recovery.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
  <FaqSection faqs={faqs} title="SMSBump Shopify FAQ" />
</BaseLayout>
